    "title": "Senior Plant Manager at Astral Pipes",
    "description": "Are you a skilled Plant Manager looking for your next big career move? Astral Pipes in Tiruchirappalli offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Astral Pipes:\nAstral Pipes is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in TPM\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Referral bonus program\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Astral Pipes!",
